entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued October 09 at 6:42AM AKDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...Elevated Surf Possible Monday Night Through Thursday... West winds of 25 to 35 mph blowing over a 600 NM fetch of open water over the Arctic Ocean and Chukchi Sea will cause elevated water levels and elevated surf along the Arctic Coast from Monday night through Thursday. This will likely lead to beach erosion along the Arctic Coast Monday night through Thursday.
